-- Six U.S. Troops in Afghanistan Killed by Gunman Posing as a Police Officer
-- B y   T o n y   C a p a c c i o
-- 2010-11-29T19:54:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-29/six-u-s-troops-in-afghanistan-killed-by-gunman-posing-as-a-police-officer.html
Six U.S. military personnel were
killed by a gunman dressed in an Afghan Border Police uniform, a
Pentagon spokesman, Colonel  David Lapan , told reporters today.  The Defense Department doesn’t have further details, Lapan
said. “We are in the next-of-kin notifications,” he said.  The gunman was killed by coalition forces, according to a
NATO  press release . The killings took place during a training
mission today in eastern Afghanistan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Tony Capaccio  in Washington at 
 acapaccio@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Silva at 
 msilva34@bloomberg.net . 